fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data.filter

Interface ILogicCriteria

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IConjunction, IDisjunction

    public interface ILogicCriteria
    Base interface for defining a logical criteria set, associated with a cell structure. This is designed as a fluent API: most methods can be easily chained together to simplify filter building.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    ICell.isSearchable()

    • Method Detail

      • toFilter

        IFilter toFilter()
        Creates an immutable filter that can be applied to the associated connector data source.
        Returns:
        the filter, constructed as an immutable snapshot of the current state of the entire logic criteria definition, starting at the top level of the logical criteria tree (even if this object represents a nested subquery).
        Since:
        1.0

      • getContext

        ICellStructure getContext()
        Gets the cell structure that provides the criteria context. The criteria context defines the cells that can be used to add criteria.
        Returns:
        the cell structure, such as a connector data source or an array-type cell.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getCriteriaCount

        int getCriteriaCount()
        Gets the number of non-recursive criteria in this logical criteria set.

        Each conjunction and each disjunction added to this criteria set adds 1 to the total criteria count.

        Returns:
        the non-negative number of criteria.
        Since:
        1.0

      • conjunction

        IConjunction conjunction()
        Creates a nested criteria set, where all criteria must match (a logical AND sub-expression). The nested criteria set is initially empty; criteria must be added.

        Note: method chaining is possible with the returned object. However, care should be taken to ensure that method chaining is applied to the appropriate criteria set (for example, avoid applying criteria to a nested criteria set, when it is intended to apply them to the parent criteria set).

        Returns:
        a new (empty) nested criteria set using logical AND semantics.
        Since:
        1.0

      • disjunction

        IDisjunction disjunction()
        Creates a nested criteria set, where all criteria must match (a logical OR sub-expression). The nested criteria set is initially empty; criteria must be added.

        Note: method chaining is possible with the returned object. However, care should be taken to ensure that method chaining is applied to the appropriate criteria set (for example, avoid applying criteria to a nested criteria set, when it is intended to apply them to the parent criteria set).

        Returns:
        a new (empty) nested criteria set using logical OR semantics.
        Since:
        1.0

      • eq

        ILogicCriteria eq(String identifier,
                  Object value)
        Adds an EQUALITY restriction to this set of criteria. For text type cells, the default comparison behavior is case-insensitive.
        Parameters:
        identifier - the identifier, such as a cell name within this context, to which this restriction applies.
        value - the value for comparison,
        Returns:
        the logic criteria object using which this method was invoked, to enable fluent method chaining.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        eq(String, String, boolean), notEq(String, Object)
